Reasoning: 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the complexity of the proposed algorithm and compares it to other existing algorithms. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new algorithm for polynomial interpolation and discusses its efficiency. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the use of Monte Carlo methods in reducing multivariate polynomial interpolation to univariate polynomial interpolation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the application of the proposed algorithm in control systems. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation): The paper discusses the use of black-box polynomial interpolation, which is a topic in symbolic computation.
